### If/Else Statements

The `if` statement executes code **only if** a condition is true.

---

### Basic `if`

```js
if (condition) {
  // Code runs if condition is true
}
```

### `if/else`

```js
if (condition) {
  // Runs if true
} else {
  // Runs if false
}
```

### `if/else if/else`

```js
if (condition1) {
  // Runs if condition1 is true
} else if (condition2) {
  // Runs if condition1 is false AND condition2 is true
} else {
  // Runs if both are false
}
```

---

### Example

```js
let score = 85;

if (score >= 90) {
  console.log("Grade: A");
} else if (score >= 80) {
  console.log("Grade: B");
} else if (score >= 70) {
  console.log("Grade: C");
} else {
  console.log("Grade: F");
}
```

---

### Nested If Statements

You can put `if` statements **inside** other `if` statements:

```js
if (age >= 18) {
  if (hasLicense) {
    console.log("You can drive");
  }
}
```

> **Readability Tip:** For simple conditions, use the ternary operator `? :`. For complex logic, use `if/else`.

